            <p>The socio-economic dynamics of Tagum City is atypical com- pared with other medium-sized cities in Mindanao, or for that matter, the rest of the country. The City has been accorded as one of the Most Competitive Medium-Sized Cities in the Philip- pines and one of the Seven Most Viable and Most Competitive Business Sites in the country.</p>
            <p>Moreover, the City has been successful in augmenting its locally generated revenues from its locally managed economic enter- prise projects reaching to as high as Php 48.9 million pesos in 2007. The revenues from the city economic enterprise have increased to Php 74.4 million pesos in 2010 or almost 24.2% of the total local income of the city which registered at 439.4 mil- lion pesos in the same year.
            </p><p>The development interventions in the City are decisively the product of a forward-looking and result-oriented leadership. In fact, the Honorable Mayor Rey T. Uy is the first elected public official to receive the prestigious Gawad Pag-asa Award from the Civil Service Commission.
                Over and above the tangible evidence of economic growth, the City of Tagum is renowned as a favorite destination for Lakbay- Aral (or educational tour) by officials and functionaries of various local government units from all over the country. Truly, the City of Tagum has prevailed as a “Destination for Learning”.
            <h3>Major destinations and cultural festivities</h3>
            <ol><li>1. Musikahan sa Tagum Festival (February 21-27) – The longest running and inclusive music festival that is participated by Filipino and foreign artists.
                </li><li>2. Durian Festival (During the Durian Fruiting Season in August to September) – Savor the King of the Fruit during the Mindan- ao’s culinary Olympics and be enthralled by the uniqueness and singularity of Durian based culinary showcases.
                </li><li>3. Tagum City River Cruise (Whole year round) – An excur- sion into the “wetlands-in-a-city” to witness the successes of the Mangrove Development and Rehabilitation Program and Community-based Tourism initiatives.
                </li></ol>

