            <h3>Tagum City’s Must Do List
            </h3><ol><li>1. Embark on the Tagum City River Cruise and revisit the significance of the “wetlands-in-the-city” and encounter the rich- ness of the cultural traditions of the local community.
                </li><li>2. Experience the Tagum City Night Market and indulge in the best food trip.
                </li><li>3. Embrace the Landmarks of the Tagum, the “Home of Festivals” – including historical, architectural and natural land- marks as well as its tourism products and the treasured Emerald Durian delicacies.
                </li><li>4. Esteem the Sustainability of the City’s Economic Enterprise Projects and the timely delivery of engineering support services.
                </li><li>5. Explore the engaging and successful Reef-to-Ridge Environmental Conservation Program. Learn on several conservation programs like coastal resource management, partnerships in watershed conservation, marine life sanctuary, barangay-based solid-waste management and the successes of the City’s Urban Greening interventions.
                </li></ol><h3>Profile</h3>
